The paper deals with completeness assessment of RDF data, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of completeness information and indexing techniques also suggests relevance to information retrieval (cs.IR) and scalable data processing (cs.SI). Finally, the development of a tool for reasoning about completeness of query answers over RDF data aligns with the sub-category of deep learning (cs.DL) which involves developing tools for reasoning and decision-making.
